<L>Thus they prefer my <HI>Va&s;&s;al</HI> me before:</L>
<L>And, but the Kingdom, what can he have more</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>From that Day forward, <HI>Saul</HI> did <HI>David</HI> eye</L>
<L>And to have &s;lain him, (divers times, did try:</L>
<L><PB N="23" REF="36">Ev'n while good <HI>David</HI> on his Harp did play,</L>
<L>The Trouble of <HI>Saul</HI>'s Spirit to allay.</L>
<L>But <HI>David</HI>'s God (who had King <HI>Saul</HI> rejected,</L>
<L>And cho&s;en <HI>David) David</HI> &s;till protected.</L>
