<LG>
<L>This was the Ruin of this goodly Prince,</L>
<L>$et loo&s;e too &s;oon; his lofty Mind, e'er &s;ince,</L>
<L>$im'd nothing <HI>lower</HI> than the <HI>highe&s;t</HI> Seat;</L>
<L>$hought nothing, for him&s;elf, too <HI>Good</HI>, too <HI>Great</HI>.</L>
<L>$e on the Crown look't with a longing Eye:</L>
<L>$or &s;pake, nor dream't of ought but Monarchy.</L>
<L>$nd when&s;o'er he &s;aw the Royal <HI>Throne</HI>,</L>
<L>$ould &s;carce forbear to call that Seat <HI>his own</HI>.</L>
<L>$is own it might have been, would he have &s;taid,</L>
<L>$ntil his Father's Head was fairly laid.</L>
